<tr class=3D"rowNormal">
<td nowrap=3D"true" class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><a href=
=3D"https://jira.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/ART-29108?src=3Dconfmacro">ART-2=
9108</a></td>
<td nowrap=3D"true" class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><!-- The=
 new status lozengens support for Jira 6.2 or later. Otherwise we use the i=
con.--> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle             aui-lozen=
ge-default
    "> Backlog </span></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport">Thomas Van Deun</td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport">Melinda Jamieson</td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><a href=3D"https://jira.=
srv.westpac.com.au/browse/ART-29108?src=3Dconfmacro"> Solution Design Decis=
ions: Do we show all available payments methods in the UI, or only 1 based =
on pre-defined order? </a></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><p>Osko and SCT is charg=
ed the same so there's no reason to give users a choice between the 2 - if =
Osko is available we always push them to Osko</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Bigger que=
stion:&nbsp; Do we only return 1 payment method from the EXP API?&nbsp;</p>=
<p>This means, no multiple options in the dropdown, it will always be popul=
ated with 1, based on this order:</p>
<ul>
<li>On-Platform (display Fast Payment)</li>
<li>Osko</li>
<li>SCT (display Fast Payment)</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"rowAlternate">
<td nowrap=3D"true" class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><a href=
=3D"https://jira.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/ART-29107?src=3Dconfmacro">ART-2=
9107</a></td>
<td nowrap=3D"true" class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><!-- The=
 new status lozengens support for Jira 6.2 or later. Otherwise we use the i=
con.--> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle             aui-lozen=
ge-success
    "> Done </span></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport">Thomas Van Deun</td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport">Thomas Van Deun</td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><a href=3D"https://jira.=
srv.westpac.com.au/browse/ART-29107?src=3Dconfmacro"> Solution Design Decis=
ions: When looking up a Creditor Service level - we ignore the outcome of '=
onUs flag' - meaning there is no way to identify an On-Platform payment </a=
></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"><p>Description:</p><p>&n=
bsp;</p><p>This endpoint, returns a flag to the UI 'OnUs'. This is a rule i=
n POM, to determine that the creditor bsb belongs within the WBC portfolio.=
 It DOES NOT identify whether the creditor is On-Me. On-Platform or On-Grou=
p. It could be any of those 3.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Currently (May 25) we cou=
ld assume that:</p>
<ul>
<li>OnUs means On-Me or On-platform, as no other BSB's are included, BUT th=
is is not future proof.</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>So, what we should do:</p>
<ul>
<li>Ignore the outcome of On-Us. For Channels to actually be able to use it=
, we need to be able to identify what type of On-Us (On-Me. On-Platform or =
On-Group). Because Channels does not have that capability, it is not safe t=
o assume what this field means.</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><del><b>That means, that when we implement this - we c=
an NEVER use the On-Platform payment method, as there is no reliable way fo=
r the Channel to identify this.</b></del>&nbsp;</p><p><del><font color=3D"#=
ff0000"><b>This is a feature gap</b></font></del></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>For no=
w, we can make the assumption that OnUs means OnPlatform.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><=
p>In the future, once FIS integrates with more OnUs BSBs this logic will ne=
ed to be updated.</p><p><b>Decision: we do NOT ignore the OnUs Flag and tre=
at it as OnPlatform.</b></p></td>
<td class=3D"jira-macro-table-underline-pdfexport"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
