<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-Non-FunctionalRequirement=
sTraceability">Non-Functional Requirements Traceability</h3>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-TechnicalDebt">Technical =
Debt</h2>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class=3D"jira-issue" data-jira-key=3D"ART-10194" data=
-client-id=3D"SINGLE_423b3ce2-7972-34d9-89b0-f76adf824219_1864174231_8ae870=
c2927e5b4c0192bccbb90e00cc"> <a href=3D"https://jira.srv.westpac.com.au/bro=
wse/ART-10194" class=3D"jira-issue-key"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-wa=
it issue-placeholder"></span>ART-10194</a> - <span class=3D"summary">Gettin=
g issue details...</span> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui=
-lozenge-default issue-placeholder">STATUS</span> </span></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-Solution"><span>Solution<=
/span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-SolutionOverview"><span>S=
olution Overview</span></h2>
<p><span>Within the W1C Portal, we make a new API call during the Payment I=
nitiation Journey. This happens after a payee has been selected (and if tha=
t is a PayId alias, after that alias is resolved).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span>In that API call, we supply the debtor bsb and schemaName, togethe=
r with the creditor bsb and schemeName OR the creditor&nbsp; PayId alias.</=
span></p>
<p><span>In the response of this API call, we get the <strong>available ser=
vice levels </strong>back. In the experience API, we will have to do some f=
iltering, because not all service levels should be returned to the customer=
 (eg unsupported ones, or PayTo). In addition to that, it will also tell us=
 whether the creditor is <strong>On-Us.</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span>This list should then be used to dynamically populate the Payment =
Method dropdown list, using the Method Name and Method code from the EXP AP=
I.<br>
 When making the payment, the values should be used from this list in the s=
ame way the static values are used now.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<ol>
<li><span>There will be some filtering needed on the EXP API, as described =
below:</span></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 82.=
173%;" data-snooker-col-series=3D"numbers" data-snooker-locked-cols=3D"0">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 2.69789%;">
<col style=3D"width: 12.9114%;">
<col style=3D"width: 14.8384%;">
<col style=3D"width: 16.9582%;">
<col style=3D"width: 17.4721%;">
<col style=3D"width: 17.4078%;">
<col style=3D"width: 0.192707%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
