<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-AUG25ERM25E3-DEUplift"><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>AUG 25 ERM25E3 &nbsp;- DE Uplift</=
strong></span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>Context: The term DE (Direct =
Entry) is the industry name. For UX purposes we call the payment method 'Pa=
y Anyone'. They are the same.</strong></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>To identify if DE is supported, look into this field of the CAP API resp=
onse: <strong>paymentSchemes.</strong></p>
<p>This is an array of strings - if "DE" is present then return according t=
o this rule <span style=3D"color: rgb(153,51,0);">If priority 1 is not ther=
e, then send DE service level alongside with priority 2 and 3</span><br>
 Example array:&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none=
;" data-teams=3D"true">paymentSchemes =3D ["NPP","DE","RTGS"]</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Return as to UI:<br><br><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">schemeEligibility[i].paymentMethod.code =3D "<strong style=3D"text=
-decoration: none;text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">=
NURG</span></strong>"</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">schemeEligibili=
ty[i].paymentMethod.description =3D "Pay Anyone"</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span>2. The experience API can actually only return &nbsp;max 2 payment=
 methods - based on the available ones. So this 'ordering' should be done a=
fter the filtering</span></p>
<p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t=
 u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak">Order should be:</span></span></p>
<ul>
<li>On-Platform (display Fast Payment) (if On-Platform is available, don't =
return DE even if its supported)</li>
<li>Osko &amp; DE</li>
<li>SCT (display Fast Payment) &amp; DE</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-AUG26ERM26E3-RTGSUplift">=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>AUG 26 ERM26E3 &nbsp;- RTGS Upli=
ft</strong></span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">To identify if RTGS is supported, loo=
k into this field of the CAP API response:&nbsp;<strong>paymentSchemes.</st=
rong></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Outstanding item</span></stro=
ng></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The ordering of display is still yet=
 to be defined.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);tex=
t-decoration: none;">schemeEligibility[i].paymentMethod.description =3D "RT=
GS"</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);tex=
t-decoration: none;">schemeEligibility[i].paymentMethod.code =3D <strong>TB=
C</strong></span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text=
-decoration: none;">As part of the feature, EXP API will need to check if t=
he creditor is Pay ID account, (<em style=3D"text-align: left;">creditorAcc=
ount.payAlias </em>is supplied), EXP API should not return RTGS in the resp=
onse object schemeEligibility[i].</span></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:LookupSchemeeligibilityforBSBs-Examplecodesnippettogetla=
testversionofaschema:"><span>Example code snippet to get latest version of =
a schema:</span></h3>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">const ge=
tHighestVersion =3D (versionList) =3D&gt; {
  let highestVersion =3D '';

  versionList.forEach(version =3D&gt; {
    // Split the version string to isolate the version number
    const versionNumber =3D version.split('.').pop();

    // Compare versions
    if (!highestVersion || parseInt(versionNumber) &gt; parseInt(highestVer=
sion.split('.').pop())) {
      highestVersion =3D version;
    }
  });

  return highestVersion;
};

// Example usage in a React component
const VersionChecker =3D () =3D&gt; {
  const versions =3D ["npp.clear.01-sct.03", "npp.clear.01-sct.04"];
  const highest =3D getHighestVersion(versions);

  return (
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;h1&gt;Highest Version: {highest}&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  );
};

export default VersionChecker;

</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
